parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cam Position Signal Output Circuit Low (P2615) - Power Loss
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cam position signal output circuit can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and make it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear
rattling sound under the shifter and center console

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engagement of limp mode can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: onset of limp mode can occur at any time
including during initial start-up and while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Loss and Limp Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and entry into limp mode can cause a significant reduction in vehicle speed, making it difficult to merge into traffic or maintain safe speeds, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and may only reach speeds of 25-30 mph; the engine may stall and then enter limp mode after restarting; the vehicle may not respond to accelerator pedal input; the check engine light may or may not be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: LIMP Mode and Reduced Power Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's sudden loss of power and acceleration can lead to accidents, especially when merging onto highways or climbing hills, and can cause inconvenience and frustration to the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls and goes into LIMP Mode
the vehicle fails to respond to accelerator pedal input
the vehicle's speed is limited to around 40 mph
the vehicle's power is significantly reduced.
